article.description: No. 12 Kansas State extended its winning streak to seven games with a 75-45 victory over Texas-San Antonio in the UTSA New Year's Classic.
article.headline: Ohlde scores 20 vs. Texas-SA
article.linkText: No. 12 Kansas State extends win streak to seven
article.story:
SAN ANTONIO, Texas (Ticker) -- Nicole Ohlde scored a game-high 
20 points and Kendra Wecker added 17 to help No. 12 Kansas State
extend its winning streak to seven games with a 75-45 victory
over Texas-San Antonio in the UTSA New Year's Classic.

Ohlde, who shot 10-of-15 from the floor, has averaged 23 points
over the past three games and has scored in double figures in
nine of the first 11 games this season for the Wildcats (9-2).

Ohlde and Wecker combined for 17 rebounds for Kansas State,
which has not lost since a 69-56 setback to Penn State on
November 29th.

Laurie Koehn chipped in 13 points and Megan Mahoney added eight
for the Wildcats, who defeated Southeast Missouri State on
Tuesday to win both games of the Texas-San Antonio Classic.

Katie Sandefur scored 19 points and Dewella Holliday contributed
11 for the Roadrunners(3-7), who have lost five of their last
six games.
